description: Erection of a podium development above the existing six storey car park comprising an additional 20 floors extending the existing structure to a part 7, part 11 and part 26 storey building, consisting of the provision of 214 residential units on the sixth to twenty six floors, reconfiguration of the existing car park layout, access and egress to retain  retail parking spaces for the shopping centre and the 26 parking spaces for the residential units. Alterations to the Myrtle Road and Thorold Road facades of the car park, creating 300sq.m of flexible commercial floor space (Class A1, A2, A3, A5 and B1 uses) at ground floor and landscaped living walls at first to fifth floors, improvements to the pedestrian entrance and link through the car park at ground floor, including associated improvements to the public realm, secured cycle storage areas, refuse, servicing and plant areas (Summary).
decision_conditions:
The development hereby permitted shall be begun not later than the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the requirements of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.
site_name: Development At The Exchange And Car Park
